---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import headshot from '../assets/headshot.jpg';
---

<MainLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Adam Sneed: security-focused engineering leader with a two-decade track record in operations, privileged access, and agentic AI systems."
>
  <section class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[320px,1fr]">
    <div class="card h-fit" data-reveal>
      <img
        src={headshot.src}
        width={headshot.width}
        height={headshot.height}
        alt="Illustrated headshot of Adam Sneed with a bookshelf background"
        class="w-full rounded-xl border border-borderTone object-cover"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1 class="section-title">Engineering every layer</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Two decades building from the physical layer up — RedHat and AIX administration, datacenter operations, enterprise networking, all the way through security engineering and now autonomous AI agents.
        </p>
        <p class="text-textMuted">
          At Netwrix, I&apos;m a Senior Solutions Architect in Professional Services — the subject matter expert on our PAM product. I design and deploy enterprise PAM solutions, build automation frameworks, and translate complex security requirements into production-grade implementations.
        </p>
        <p class="text-textMuted">
          Outside of that, I engineer across all three layers. Physical: home lab infrastructure, edge devices, custom hardware rigs. Software: APIs, integration pipelines, automation systems that hold under pressure. Agentic: multi-agent orchestration, prompt engineering, and autonomous workflows built with the same discipline I bring to privileged access — least privilege, human oversight, audit trails, fail-safe defaults.
        </p>
        <p class="border-l-2 border-accent/40 pl-4 text-lg text-textMain">
          Each layer informs the next. Infrastructure discipline shapes software design. Software discipline shapes agent design. That&apos;s the through-line.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card border-l-4 border-l-accent/40" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="mb-4 font-mono text-xl font-semibold">Operating Principles</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-textMuted">
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-accent"></span><span>Build for production, not demos.</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-accent"></span><span>Security is architecture, not a feature.</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-accent"></span><span>Agents need guardrails.</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-accent"></span><span>Write it down.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="mb-3 font-mono text-xl font-semibold">Policy Lens</h2>
        <p class="text-textMuted">
          My Juris Doctor from LSU Law informs how I design policies, evaluate regulatory risk, and write statement-of-work
          scope with contract-level precision.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
